Reasoning: The paper proposes algorithms for real-time anomaly detection in high-dimensional settings, which involves machine learning and data analysis techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with security and intrusion detection, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed algorithms are nonparametric and model-free, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. The paper also deals with data streams, which suggests the involvement of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
